        <type><ref refid="syn__defs_8h_1af6a258d8f3ee5206d682d799316314b1" kindref="member">bool</ref></type>
        <definition>bool syn_stream_readable</definition>
        <argsstring>(const SYN_Stream *s)</argsstring>
        <name>syn_stream_readable</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="structSYN__Stream" kindref="compound">SYN_Stream</ref> *</type>
          <declname>s</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Check if the stream is readable (mode-aware). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Behavior depends on configured mode:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Delimiter mode</bold>: true if the delimiter byte is in the buffer.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Threshold mode</bold>: true if count &gt;= threshold.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Default</bold>: true if any bytes are available.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Delimiter mode takes precedence over threshold mode.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>s</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Stream instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>true if the stream has data meeting the readability criteria. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
